It was a dream come true for the Raw Materials Research and Development Council (RMRDC) as it hosted and won the gold medal of the football event at the just concluded 17th Research Institutes Games after defeating the Nigerian Institute for Oil Palm Research (NIFOR) 3-1 in the final. The Forestry Research Institute of Nigeria (FRIN) of Ibadan emerged the overall winner of the 2022 Games held at the Area 10 Parade Ground in Garki and Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja. The Games which came to a thrilling end at the weekend featured 998 participants from 22 research institutes. RIGAN president, Professor Feranmi Owolade, told reporters that while RMRDC won gold in the finals of the football match, the Ibadan-based FRIN for the second time emerged the overall winner with 20 gold, 16 silver and 16 bronze. The Nigerian Veterinary Research Institute (NVRI), in Vom near Jos, finished second with 12 gold, 26 silver and 10 bronze while the Institute of Agricultural Research and Training/Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU) came third with 12 gold, 5 silver and 7 bronze. 